OL,3,CHouseholds urged to send in meter
OL,4,Creadings ahead of Oct 1 price hike
OL,6,FAlmost 10 million households have been
OL,7,Fwarned they risk overpaying for their
OL,8,Fenergy if they do not send meter
OL,9,Freadings to their supplier before a
OL,10,F10% price rise takes effect on October
OL,11,F1.
OL,13,FThe average household energy bill is
OL,14,Fto increase by #149 a year from
OL,15,FTuesday as Ofgem increases its price
OL,16,Fcap just as homes move into the winter
OL,17,Fmonths.
