OL,3,CHouseholds urged to send in meter
OL,4,Creadings ahead of Oct 1 price hike
OL,6,FThose households on a standard
OL,7,Fvariable tariff (SVT) ` as opposed to
OL,8,Fa fixed deal ` and who do not have a
OL,9,Fsmart meter should submit their
OL,10,Felectricity and gas readings to their
OL,11,Fsupplier as close as possible to
OL,12,FOctober 1 to ensure any energy they
OL,13,Fuse before this date is not
OL,14,Finaccurately billed at the higher
OL,15,Fprices.
OL,17,FSuppliers who have not received meter
OL,18,Freadings base their bills on estimated
OL,19,Fusage, meaning households could be
OL,20,Foverpaying, while others may not be
OL,21,Fpaying enough.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
