OL,3,CHouseholds urged to send in meter
OL,4,Creadings ahead of Oct 1 price hike
OL,6,FThe price cap sets a maximum price
OL,7,Fthat energy suppliers can charge
OL,8,Fconsumers for each kilowatt hour (kWh)
OL,9,Fof energy they use.
OL,11,FIt does not limit total bills because
OL,12,Fhouseholders still pay for the amount
OL,13,Fof energy they consume.
OL,15,FFrom October 1, households on a
OL,16,Fstandard variable tariff that pay for
OL,17,Ftheir electricity by direct debit will
OL,18,Fpay on average 24.5p per unit, with a
OL,19,Fstanding charge of 60.99p per day.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
